Podcasts Blogs CONTACT ABOUT US Staff Coverage Advantage Partners Employment LINKS LISTEN LIVE Home > News Two-Vehicle Fatal Crash on State Route 339 Posted on: 03/04/2022 By Brett Wharff & Jacob Krantz VINCENT, OH- A two-vehicle fatal crash occurred Thursday night near the corner of State Route 339 and County Road 806. Involved in the crash was a 1996 Honda Civic being operated by 20-year-old Dylan Ours of Waterford. The other vehicle involved was a 1999 Chevy Blazer being Operated by 22-year-old Timothie Haught of Vincent. The investigation found that Haught in the Blazer was traveling northbound on State Route 339 and was attempting to turn left onto Spence Lane, according to the Marietta Post of the Ohio State Highway Patrol. Reports claim Haught failed to yield to southbound traffic and was struck by Ours in the Civic. Both Haught and Ours reportedly sustained non-life-threatening injuries as a result of the crash. A juvenile passenger in Haught's Blazer was flown to Nationwide Children's Hospital with serious injuries. Reports also say that in the Civic, a 19-year-old Joslyn Trent of Marietta sustained life threatening injuries and was transported to Camden Clark Medical Center where she was pronounced deceased. The Ohio State Highway Patrol, Dunham Township Volunteer Fire Department, Wesley Township Volunteer Fire Department, Barlow Volunteer Fire Department and Washington County Sheriff's Office responded to the scene. WMOA News was on scene last night as well. Alcohol is not suspected to be a factor in the crash. The use of seatbelts is still being investigated. The Marietta Post of the Ohio State Highway Patrol is leading the investigation. Local News Two-Vehicle Fatal Crash on State Route 339 The accident occurred approximately 8:00 p.m. Thursday. (NCD) Country singer Toby Keith announced Sunday on social media that he has been privately battling stomach cancer. >> Read more trending news The “As Good as I Once Was” singer, 60, posted on Twitter that he had cancer and has spent the last six months receiving chemotherapy, WKRN-TV reported. “Last fall I was diagnosed with stomach cancer,” Keith wrote, “I’ve spent the last six months receiving chemo, radiation, and surgery. So far, so good. I need time to breathe, recover and relax. “I am looking forward to spending this time with my family, but I will see the fans sooner than later. I can’t wait.” pic.twitter.com/TeADP7UN8h Keith has been a force on the Billboard country music charts, scoring 20 No. 1 hits. He has an additional 21 songs that have reached Billboard’s top-10 and has charted 61 country singles overall. His 2003 duet with Willie Nelson, “Beer for My Horses,” stayed at No. 1 for six weeks. “As Good as I Once Was,” released in 2005, also topped the charts for six weeks. Other No. 1 hits for Keith include his breakthrough 1993 hit, “Should’ve Been a Cowboy,” according to the Songwriters Hall of Fame. Keith, who was inducted into the Hall in 2015, also scored No. 1 hits with “I Love This Bar,” “How Do You Like Me Now?!,” “Who’s Your Daddy?,” “American Soldier” and “Courtesy of the Red, White and Blue (The Angry American).” “Courtesy of the Red, White and Blue” was Keith’s response to the Sept. 11 terrorist attacks and was a crossover hit in 2002, reaching No. 25 on Billboard’s Hot 100 chart. He is the founder and President of the Avila Institute for Spiritual Formation, which offers graduate and personal enrichment studies in spiritual theology to priests, deacons, religious, and laity in 90 countries and prepares men for seminary in over 40 dioceses. Dan is the author and editor of numerous books on authentic Catholic spirituality and hosts the Divine Intimacy Radio show with his wife, Stephanie, which is broadcast weekly on EWTN Radio. Past episodes can be found, along with thousands of articles on the interior life, at SpiritualDirection.com. In his deep commitment to the advancement of faithful Catholic spirituality, he is also the founder of Apostoli Viae, a world-wide, private association of the faithful dedicated to living and advancing the authentic spiritual patrimony of the Church. Most importantly, Dan is a blessed husband, father of four, grandfather of one—and grateful to be Catholic. Stephanie Burke Stephanie Burke is wife to Dan Burke, mother of four and grandmother of one. She co-hosts, along with Dan, the popular weekly Divine Intimacy Radio program. Together they serve as servant leaders of the Avila Foundation and the community of Apostoli Viae. In that capacity, Stephanie devotes the majority of her time in spiritual direction and deliverance ministry and is privileged to see the fruits of the healing and liberating power of God unleashed in the lives of individuals and marriages at their talks, retreats, conferences, and online events.'}]
